9 ounce Fully Cooked Chicken Breasts
1 unit Baby Lettuce
1 unit Tomato
3 ounce Buttermilk Ranch Dressing
1 teaspoon Garlic Powder
1.5 tablespoon Sour Cream
1 tablespoon Cajun Spice Blend
4 ounce Shredded Carrots
Salt
Pepper

• Wash and dry produce. Pat chicken dry with paper towels; dice into
½-inch pieces. Trim and discard root end from lettuce; roughly chop
into bite-size pieces. Dice tomato into ½-inch pieces.

• In a medium bowl, combine chicken, half of one packet dressing (one
whole packet for 4 servings), half the garlic powder, salt, and pepper.
Set aside.

• In a large bowl, combine sour cream, Cajun Spice Blend, remaining
dressing, and remaining garlic powder. Add water 1 tsp at a time
until the mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and
pepper. Add lettuce, tomato, and carrots to bowl; toss to coat. Taste
and season with salt and pepper if desired.

• Divide salad between bowls. Top with chicken mixture and serve.